Upstream released stunnel 5.79 without bumping src/version.h: the
stunnel-5.79 git tag (commit 22968e10e0dc0e653f1641131afac610b8fb63bb),
the official https://www.stunnel.org/downloads/stunnel-5.79.tar.gz
tarball, and current master all still define VERSION_MINOR 78, so the
5.79 release banners itself as "stunnel 5.78" (version.h was last
changed in the stunnel-5.78 release commit, see
https://github.com/mtrojnar/stunnel/commits/master/src/version.h).
Set the minor version to 79 so the binary reports the version it was
released and tagged as. Drop this patch once upstream ships a release
whose version.h matches its tag again.

diff --git a/src/version.h b/src/version.h
--- a/src/version.h
+++ b/src/version.h
@@ -66,4 +66,4 @@
 /* START CUSTOMIZE */
 #define VERSION_MAJOR 5
-#define VERSION_MINOR 78
+#define VERSION_MINOR 79
 /* END CUSTOMIZE */
